When formatting your prompt, start with ‘###Instruction###’, followed by either ‘###Example###’ or ‘###Question###’ if relevant. Subsequently, present your content. Use one or more line breaks to separate instructions, examples, questions, context, and input data.

Here are examples demonstrating how to apply this principle:

original: Provide a synonym for a given adjective. What’s another word for "happy"?
improved: ###Instruction###\nProvide a synonym for a given adjective.\n### Question ###\nWhat\'s another word for "happy"?

========
